  , issueCommentBody =
      "I think we should expand map to work like so:\r\n```rb\r\ntbl.map{|row| ...} # as now\r\ntbl.map{|row, idx| ...} # map with an index\r\nr.map(tbl1, tbl2){|row1, row2| ...} # map over multiple sequences\r\nr.map(tbl1, tbl2, tbl3){|row1, row2, row3| ...} # takes any number of sequences\r\nr.map(tbl1, tbl2){|row1, row2, idx| ...} # you can always take one more argument than the number of sequences to map with an index\r\n```\r\n\r\n`r.range` may be useful for other reasons, but I don't think it's the most pleasant solution to this particular problem."
